  "curation": {
    "synopsis": "In Imperium Nihilus, Angron's return is less a miracle than a wound torn open across half a million abandoned worlds. His scattered World Eaters answer the Red Angel's call, but the Legion he summons is already breaking in three directions: Kossolax the Foresworn tries to hold command aboard the flagship while fearing the father he worships, Ortan Leidis of the Angels of the Grail sees in the slaughter a ladder out of petty raiding, and Grey Knight Graucis Telomane moves against plans six centuries in the making. Dense daemon-Primarch war-psychology, Legion politics, and a counter-strike aimed at ending the Emperor's most terrible son.",
